label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of renal pelvis and ureter cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal pelvis and ureter cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Pathologic staging depends on histologic determination of the extent of invasion by the primary tumor.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal pelvis and ureter cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer pTa TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer with a finding of papillary noninvasive carcinoma. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage IV Centroblastic Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage IV: Diffuse or disseminated involvement of one or more extralymphatic organs, with or without associated lymph node involvement; or isolated extralymphatic organ involvement in the absence of adjacent regional lymph node involvement, but in conjunction with disease in distant site(s); or any involvement of the liver or bone marrow, lungs (other than by direct extension from another site), or cerebrospinal fluid.

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer pTis TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer with tumor invading subepithelial connective tissue. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer with tumor invading the muscularis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: For renal pelvis cancer only: tumor invading beyond muscularis into peripelvic fat or the renal parenchyma.  For ureter cancer only: tumor invading beyond muscularis into periureteric fat. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer with tumor invading adjacent organs, or through the kidney into the perinephric fat. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal pelvis and ureter cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.  Note: laterality does not affect the N classification. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer with no regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer with metastasis in a single lymph node, 2 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer pN2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer with metastasis in a single lymph node, more than 2 cm but not more than 5 cm in greatest dimension; or multiple lymph nodes, none more than 5 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage 0 Colorectal Cancer AJCC v6 and v7

value.value: Stage 0 includes: Tis, N0, M0.  Tis: Carcinoma in situ: intraepithelial or invasion of the lamina propria.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 6th and 7th eds.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer with metastasis in a lymph node, more than 5 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal pelvis and ureter cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for renal pelvis and ureter cancer. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of renal pelvis and ureter cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Primary tumor assessment includes radiographic imaging, usually by intravenous and/or retrograde pyelography.  Computerized tomography scanning can be used to assess regional nodes.  Ureteroscopic visualization of the tumor is desirable, and tissue biopsy through the ureteroscope may be performed if feasible.  Urine cytology may help determine tumor grade if tissue is not available. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of renal pelvis and ureter cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Renal pelvis and ureter cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Be

value.value: The state or fact of existing at a place and time.

label.value: Pediatric Disorder

value.value: A non-neoplastic or neoplastic disorder which occurs during infancy, childhood, or adolescence.

label.value: Conduct Disorder

value.value: A disorder diagnosed in childhood or adolescence age group characterized by aggressive behavior, deceitfulness, destruction of property or violation of rules that is persistent and repetitive, and within a one year period.

label.value: Metastatic Pancreatic Adenocarcinoma

value.value: An adenocarcinoma that arises from the exocrine pancreatic tissue and has metastasized to other anatomic sites.

label.value: Developmental Disorder

value.value: A disorder diagnosed in childhood that is marked by either physical or mental impairment or both, which in turn affects the child from achieving age related developmental milestones.

label.value: Early Adolescence

value.value: A human life stage that begins at twelve years of age and continues until eighteen complete years of age. This phase marks the start of physical, physiological and psychological changes that characterize pubertal growth and development.

label.value: Eating Disorder

value.value: A broad group of psychological disorders with abnormal eating behaviors leading to physiological effects from overeating or insufficient food intake.

label.value: Term Infant

value.value: An age group comprised of infants greater than or equal to 37 weeks, 0 days and less than or equal to 41 weeks, 6 days gestational age.

label.value: Learning Disorder

value.value: A group of disorders that affect a person's ability to learn or process specific types of information which is in contrast to his/her apparent level of intellect.

label.value: Life Stage

value.value: A designation assigned to a particular period during a life cycle, generally defined by chronological parameters.

label.value: Maternal

value.value: A designation that has some relationship to motherhood.

label.value: Congenital Musculoskeletal Defect

value.value: An abnormality of the musculoskeletal system that is present at birth or detected in the neonatal period.

label.value: Neurodevelopmental Disorder

value.value: A childhood disorder that has a neurological basis and manifests as a developmental disability.

label.value: Neurological Screening

value.value: A specific type of neurologic examination for early detection of disease(s) and/or disorder(s).

label.value: Metastatic Small Intestinal Adenocarcinoma

value.value: An adenocarcinoma that arises from the small intestine and has metastasized to other anatomic sites.

label.value: Obstetric Procedure

value.value: Any pregnancy or childbirth related procedure associated with a mother during her reproductive years.

label.value: Preconception

value.value: The time period prior to conception.

label.value: Toddler

value.value: An age group comprised of individuals between 12 and 18 months of age.

label.value: Finnegan Score Measurement

value.value: A tool to evaluate neonatal abstinence syndrome (NAS), that measures the degree to which a neonate is experiencing symptoms of withdrawal due to maternal substance abuse.

label.value: Late Adolescence

value.value: A human life stage that begins at nineteen years of age and continues until twenty-one complete years of age. This phase includes the final stages of pubertal growth and development as well as the attainment of significant psycho-social milestones.

label.value: Childhood

value.value: A time period that begins at the beginning of the human embryonic stage and continues until the end of adolescence.

label.value: Early Childhood

value.value: A human life stage that begins at two years of age and continues until five complete years of age.

label.value: Middle Childhood

value.value: A human life stage that begins at six years of age and continues until eleven complete years of age.

label.value: Aluminum Zirconium Trichlorohydrex Gly
Bladder Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of bladder cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.
